text.__SUMMARY__: Acacia graniticola is a shrub belonging to the genus Acacia and the subgenus Phyllodineae. It is native to an area in the Goldfields-Esperance and Weatbelt regions of Western Australia.The intricate spreading shrub typically grows to a height of 1.5 to 3.0 metres (5 to 10 ft) and produces yellow flowers from August to October.
